India's publicly-owned railway network says it has received 28 million online applications for its biggest ever recruitment drive, which ends on Saturday. The Times of India reported that railway officials expect the number of applicants for the 90,000 positions to climb even higher as the deadline approaches. The jobs advertised include 26,502 train driver and technician posts, and 62,907 vacancies for less-skilled positions including trackmen, welders and porters. Read more: India: Thousands of bags misplaced at Delhi airport Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
